# Workflow Skill Router Plugin

Workflow Skill Router is a pre-execution Skill-selection layer for Codex. It
classifies work as Single, Phased, or Managed Goal work, discovers the
available capabilities, and selects the smallest sufficient Skill set without
replacing runtime permissions, approval policies, or tool access controls.

This standalone repository contains Plugin version `{{VERSION}}`, generated
from canonical source revision `{{SOURCE_REVISION}}`.

## Install

Install this repository as a Codex Plugin from its repository root. The root
contains the Plugin manifest, Skill, bundled MCP server, and deterministic
Python runtime needed at execution time.

## Validate

```powershell
npm ci
npm run check
node scripts/smoke-plugin.mjs
```

The Plugin stores routing state outside its installation directory. See
`PRIVACY.md`, `SECURITY.md`, and `UPSTREAM.md` for operational boundaries and
source provenance.
